reviews.text:
Amici is a Contemporary European Restaurant, showcases modern yet classically inspired European Cuisine.  It delivers an intimate environment exuding simplicity and a touch of sophistication.  
.
.
Complimentary Bread & Pizza with olive oil and aged balsamic vinegar.
.
.
Sea Scallops and Tuna Tartare (HK$178)
Our starter was a delightful Tuna Tartare, served with sea scallops, avocado, black sesame and salmon roe on top.   This appetiser was packed with complexity and had many layers of flavour.
 .
.
Scallops, Avocado and Cucumber Salad (HK$168)
This is the green salad with avocado and two seared scallops.  By using Seaweed and Mirin Vanaigrette, which gave the dish an added boost of flavour and a delicious Japanese vibe to it.
.
.
Slow-cooked Iberico Pork Chop (HK$368)
For mains, the slow-cooked Iberico Pork was extremely succulent, rested on a pile of mixed veggies and served with Truffle Sauce.  The pork chop itself was packed with intense flavours and full of rich texture.
.
.
Sardines Spaghetti (HK$198)
The Spaghetti came with Shrimps, Sardines Fish and Anchovies, all those seafood created a wonderful briny flavour.  An additional ingredient added really impressed me, it was “salicornia” aka sea asparagus, the crunchiness and the saltiness of this veggie complimented the food from the sea perfectly.  
.
.
Earl Grey Oreo Cheese Cake (HK$88)
For a sweet ending, the Earl Grey Oreo Cheese Cake is a great choice, beautifully rich but light texture!
.
.
not bad... good for a sort break
good food
Very good food

The place was pretty full on a weekday. Dining area is small and the tables are packed tightly together. Their decor is an eye sore, the hanging framed artwork, sculptural lighting and wall pieces were terribly mismatching. Feels like they tried too hard to fill the empty walls or deter people's visuals from the structural piping. Luckily, the food was much better. A little bit over seasoned for my taste. We ordered the dinner set that comes w/ an appetizer, soup, main and dessert w/ tea/coffee for HK$4XX. Ordered a bottle of white wine - drinkable but nothing spectacular given the price.  Everything was decent for the price especially given 15%OFF when you book through Openrice.
1 star for decor effort
3 stars for taste
4 stars for service - servers were polite & helpful

result.name: Amici European Cuisine

reviews.text:
放工和同事在中環食飯再回家，來到了同事的飯堂Amici。餐廳不大，一目了然，裝修簡潔清雅。

餐包先上，應是自家制的，鬆軟帶香草香味，點少許黑醋已經好好食。前菜是風乾黑毛豬火腿配西瓜芝士和大閘蟹餅。
  
火腿富鹹香，配上西瓜食，又甜又咸，清新又好食。大閘蟹餅大大件，炸得十分金黃香脆，切開入面是絲絲蟹肉，很足料。
  
一旁的淺黃色的子薑檸檬泡沫，是蟹餅的精髓!!香口的蟹餅點上酸酸甜甜的它，異常合襯!!! 餐湯是粟米忌廉湯，淡黃色的creamy得黎又清甜。
  
主菜是手工蟹肉義大利面和慢煮紐西蘭牛柳配鵝肝。自家制義大利面關較粗身，伴著面頭上滿滿的蟹肉醬，啖啖肉又滋味！
  
牛柳是medium rare的，所以仍見嫩紅色，入口牛味濃，鵝肝比較厚，兩面煎得焦黃，中間juicy。
  
甜品是焦糖燴啤梨配雲呢嗱雪糕，最特別的是用上了黑醋中和甜味，食起黎頗開胃，是一新鮮的嘗試。簡簡單單的，沒有很華麗，小店的用心，令放工的我們，食得很舒心。
環境清靜，佈置優雅，食物質素有水準，但價錢略貴。
